	<refnamediv>
		<refname>mean</refname>

		<refpurpose>mean of pixel values of image</refpurpose>
	</refnamediv>

	<refsynopsisdiv>
		<title>Calling Sequence</title>

		<synopsis> x=mean(source)</synopsis>
	</refsynopsisdiv>
	
	<refsection>

		<title>Parameters</title>

		<variablelist>                                                                            
			<varlistentry><term>source:</term>
				<listitem><para> list of pixels of input image.</para></listitem></varlistentry>      
                         <varlistentry><term>x:</term>        
				<listitem><para> output mean returned by function.</para></listitem></varlistentry>          
		</variablelist>

	</refsection>



	<refsection>
		<title>Description</title>

		<para>mean of pixel values of image </para>
	
		<para>The function calculates means of pixel values of an image.It works both for RGB and gray scale image.</para>

		<para>It is expected that the user input should be a list of pixels of source image which can RGB image or gray scale image and the function will mean of all those pixel values  as output in scilab console.For RGB image this function will return total mean of all three channels.
		</para>
		
	</refsection>

	<refsection>
		<title>Examples</title>

		<programlisting role="example">b=rgb2gray(a)</programlisting>
	</refsection>

	<refsection>
		<title>Authors</title>

		<simplelist type="vert">
			<member>Priyanka Hiranandani</member>
